The City of Johannesburg is taking the fight to those involved in destroying critical infrastructure. eNCA reporter Manqoba Mchunu explains the story. Courtesy of #DStv403 ROODEPOORT - Roodepoort ward 127 councillor, Keke Tabane said there appears to be a cable theft syndicate operating in the area given the spate of power outages. Theft and vandalism result in blackouts in several areas, leaving many without electricity for days on end. READ:Â SA's electricity crisis | Group demands action on promises Tabane said, "our community has been without power for the past three days, we've got businesses in the area that has been affected and members of the community." "Looking at the operation, I can say that there are possibilities that these people are coming from a well organised activity...I've engaged the MMC to say we need to find a way of securing this mini-substation because it happens most of the time around this area."